61 gentity_t *Weapon_Knife(gentity_t *ent)
62 {
63  trace_t tr;
64  gentity_t *traceEnt, *tent;
65  int damage;
66  meansOfDeath_t mod = GetWeaponTableData(ent->s.weapon)->mod;
67  vec3_t end;
68 
69  AngleVectors(ent->client->ps.viewangles, forward, right, up);
70  CalcMuzzlePoint(ent, ent->s.weapon, forward, right, up, muzzleTrace);
71  VectorMA(muzzleTrace, CH_KNIFE_DIST, forward, end);
72  G_HistoricalTrace(ent, &tr, muzzleTrace, NULL, NULL, end, ent->s.number, MASK_SHOT);
73 
74  // ignore hits on NOIMPACT surfaces or no contact
75  if ((tr.surfaceFlags & SURF_NOIMPACT) || tr.fraction == 1.0f)
76  {
77  return NULL;
78  }
79 
80  if (tr.entityNum >= MAX_CLIENTS) // world brush or non-player entity (no blood)
81  {
82  tent = G_TempEntity(tr.endpos, EV_MISSILE_MISS);
83  }
84  else // other player
85  {
86  tent = G_TempEntity(tr.endpos, EV_MISSILE_HIT);
87  }
88 
89  tent->s.otherEntityNum = tr.entityNum;
90  tent->s.eventParm = DirToByte(tr.plane.normal);
91  tent->s.weapon = ent->s.weapon;
92  tent->s.clientNum = ent->r.ownerNum;
93 
94  if (tr.entityNum == ENTITYNUM_WORLD) // don't worry about doing any damage
95  {
96  return NULL;
97  }
98 
99  traceEnt = &g_entities[tr.entityNum];
100 
101  if (!(traceEnt->takedamage))
102  {
103  return NULL;
104  }
105 
106  damage = GetWeaponTableData(ent->s.weapon)->damage; // default knife damage for frontal attacks (10)
107 
108  // no damage
109  if (!damage)
110  {
111  return NULL;
112  }
113 
114  // Covert ops deal double damage with a knife
115  if (ent->client->sess.playerType == PC_COVERTOPS)
116  {
117  damage <<= 1; // damage *= 2; // Watch it - you could hurt someone with that thing!
118 
119  }
120  // removed not allowing insta-gib backstabs on wounded players (CHRUKER: b002 "fix")
121  if (traceEnt->client) // && traceEnt->health > 0)
122  {
123  if (G_GetEnemyPosition(ent, traceEnt) == POSITION_BEHIND) // from behind(-ish)
124  {
125  // enough to drop a 'normal' (100 health) human with one jab
126  // (not for real if there is a medic in the team because of medic MP bonus)
127  damage = 100;
128  mod = MOD_BACKSTAB;
129 
130  if (ent->client->sess.skill[SK_MILITARY_INTELLIGENCE_AND_SCOPED_WEAPONS] >= 4)
131  {
132  if (traceEnt->health > 0)
133  {
134  damage = traceEnt->health;
135  }
136  else if (traceEnt->health <= 0) // allow 'instagib' on wounded players
137  {
138  damage = traceEnt->health - GIB_HEALTH;
139  }
140  }
141  }
142  }
143 
144  // FIXME: should we keep this random add ?!
145  G_Damage(traceEnt, ent, ent, vec3_origin, tr.endpos, (damage + rand() % 5), 0, mod);
146 
147  return NULL;
148 }

323 void ReviveEntity(gentity_t *ent, gentity_t *traceEnt)
324 {
325  vec3_t org;
326  trace_t tr;
327  int healamt, headshot, oldweapon, oldclasstime = 0;
328  int ammo[MAX_WEAPONS]; // total amount of ammo
329  int ammoclip[MAX_WEAPONS]; // ammo in clip
330  int weapons[MAX_WEAPONS / (sizeof(int) * 8)]; // 64 bits for weapons held
331 
332  // heal the dude
333  // copy some stuff out that we'll wanna restore
334  VectorCopy(traceEnt->client->ps.origin, org);
335 
336  headshot = traceEnt->client->ps.eFlags & EF_HEADSHOT;
337 
338  if (ent->client->sess.skill[SK_FIRST_AID] >= 3)
339  {
340  healamt = traceEnt->client->ps.stats[STAT_MAX_HEALTH];
341  }
342  else
343  {
344  healamt = (int)(traceEnt->client->ps.stats[STAT_MAX_HEALTH] * 0.5);
345  }
346 
347  oldweapon = traceEnt->client->ps.weapon;
348 
349  // keep class special weapon time to keep them from exploiting revives
350  oldclasstime = traceEnt->client->ps.classWeaponTime;
351 
352  Com_Memcpy(ammo, traceEnt->client->ps.ammo, sizeof(int) * MAX_WEAPONS);
353  Com_Memcpy(ammoclip, traceEnt->client->ps.ammoclip, sizeof(int) * MAX_WEAPONS);
354  Com_Memcpy(weapons, traceEnt->client->ps.weapons, sizeof(int) * (MAX_WEAPONS / (sizeof(int) * 8)));
355 
356  ClientSpawn(traceEnt, qtrue, qfalse, qtrue);
357 
358 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
359  Bot_Event_Revived(traceEnt - g_entities, ent);
360 #endif
361 
362  traceEnt->client->ps.stats[STAT_PLAYER_CLASS] = traceEnt->client->sess.playerType;
363  Com_Memcpy(traceEnt->client->ps.ammo, ammo, sizeof(int) * MAX_WEAPONS);
364  Com_Memcpy(traceEnt->client->ps.ammoclip, ammoclip, sizeof(int) * MAX_WEAPONS);
365  Com_Memcpy(traceEnt->client->ps.weapons, weapons, sizeof(int) * (MAX_WEAPONS / (sizeof(int) * 8)));
366 
367  if (headshot)
368  {
369  traceEnt->client->ps.eFlags |= EF_HEADSHOT;
370  }
371 
372  traceEnt->client->ps.weapon = oldweapon;
373  traceEnt->client->ps.weaponstate = WEAPON_READY;
374  traceEnt->client->ps.classWeaponTime = oldclasstime;
375 
376  // set idle animation on weapon
377  traceEnt->client->ps.weapAnim = PM_IdleAnimForWeapon(traceEnt->client->ps.weapon);
378 
379  traceEnt->health = healamt;
380  VectorCopy(org, traceEnt->s.origin);
381  VectorCopy(org, traceEnt->r.currentOrigin);
382  VectorCopy(org, traceEnt->client->ps.origin);
383 
384  trap_Trace(&tr, traceEnt->client->ps.origin, traceEnt->client->ps.mins, traceEnt->client->ps.maxs, traceEnt->client->ps.origin, traceEnt->s.number, MASK_PLAYERSOLID);
385  if (tr.allsolid)
386  {
387  traceEnt->client->ps.pm_flags |= PMF_DUCKED;
388  }
389 
390  traceEnt->r.contents = CONTENTS_CORPSE;
391  trap_LinkEntity(ent);
392 
393  // Let the person being revived know about it
394  trap_SendServerCommand(traceEnt - g_entities, va("cp \"You have been revived by [lof]%s[lon] [lof]%s^7!\"", GetRankTableData(ent->client->sess.sessionTeam, ent->client->sess.rank)->names, ent->client->pers.netname));
395 
396  traceEnt->props_frame_state = ent->s.number;
397 
398  // sound
399  G_Sound(traceEnt, GAMESOUND_MISC_REVIVE);
400 
401  traceEnt->client->pers.lastrevive_client = ent->s.clientNum;
402  traceEnt->client->pers.lasthealth_client = ent->s.clientNum;
403 
404  if (g_fastres.integer > 0)
405  {
406  BG_AnimScriptEvent(&traceEnt->client->ps, traceEnt->client->pers.character->animModelInfo, ANIM_ET_JUMP, qfalse, qtrue);
407  }
408  else
409  {
410  // Play revive animation
411  BG_AnimScriptEvent(&traceEnt->client->ps, traceEnt->client->pers.character->animModelInfo, ANIM_ET_REVIVE, qfalse, qtrue);
412  traceEnt->client->ps.pm_flags |= PMF_TIME_LOCKPLAYER;
413  traceEnt->client->ps.pm_time = 2100;
414  }
415 }

424 gentity_t *Weapon_Syringe(gentity_t *ent)
425 {
426  vec3_t end;
427  trace_t tr;
428  gentity_t *traceEnt;
429 
430  AngleVectors(ent->client->ps.viewangles, forward, right, up);
431  CalcMuzzlePointForActivate(ent, forward, right, up, muzzleTrace);

433  // right on top of intended revivee.
434  G_HistoricalTrace(ent, &tr, muzzleTrace, NULL, NULL, end, ent->s.number, MASK_SHOT);
435 
436  if (tr.startsolid)
437  {
438  VectorMA(muzzleTrace, 8, forward, end);
439  trap_Trace(&tr, muzzleTrace, NULL, NULL, end, ent->s.number, MASK_SHOT);

441 
442  if (tr.fraction == 1.0f) // no hit
443  {
444  // give back ammo

446  return NULL;
447  }
448 
449  traceEnt = &g_entities[tr.entityNum];
450 
451  if (!traceEnt->client)
452  {
453  // give back ammo
454  ent->client->ps.ammoclip[GetWeaponTableData(WP_MEDIC_SYRINGE)->clipIndex] += 1;
455  return NULL;
456  }
457 
458  if (traceEnt->client->ps.pm_type == PM_DEAD &&
459  traceEnt->client->sess.sessionTeam == ent->client->sess.sessionTeam)
460  {
461  // moved all the revive stuff into its own function
462  ReviveEntity(ent, traceEnt);
463 
464  // syringe "hit"
465  // we no longer track the syringe - it's no real weapon and messes up the total weapon stats (see acc)
466  // FIXME: add a new award 'most revives' instead?
467  //if (g_gamestate.integer == GS_PLAYING)
468  //{
469  //ent->client->sess.aWeaponStats[WS_SYRINGE].hits++;
470  //}
471 
472  G_LogPrintf("Medic_Revive: %d %d\n", (int)(ent - g_entities), (int)(traceEnt - g_entities));
473 
474  if (!traceEnt->isProp) // flag for if they were teamkilled or not
475  {
476  G_AddSkillPoints(ent, SK_FIRST_AID, 4.f);
477  G_DebugAddSkillPoints(ent, SK_FIRST_AID, 4.f, "reviving a player");
478  }
479 
480  // calculate ranks to update numFinalDead arrays. Have to do it manually as addscore has an early out
481  if (g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS)
482  {
483  CalculateRanks();
484  }
485  }
486  else
487  {
488  // If the medicine wasn't used, give back the ammo
489  ent->client->ps.ammoclip[GetWeaponTableData(WP_MEDIC_SYRINGE)->clipIndex] += 1;
490  }
491 
492  return NULL;
493 }

513 int EntsThatRadiusCanDamage(vec3_t origin, float radius, int *damagedList)
514 {
515  float dist;
516  gentity_t *ent;
517  int entityList[MAX_GENTITIES];
518  int numListedEntities;
519  vec3_t mins, maxs;
520  vec3_t v;
521  int i, e;
522  float boxradius;
523  vec3_t dest;
524  trace_t tr;
525  vec3_t midpoint;
526  int numDamaged = 0;
527 
528  if (radius < 1)
529  {
530  radius = 1;
531  }
532 
533  boxradius = M_SQRT2 * radius; // radius * sqrt(2) for bounding box enlargement --
534  // bounding box was checking against radius / sqrt(2) if collision is along box plane
535  for (i = 0 ; i < 3 ; i++)
536  {
537  mins[i] = origin[i] - boxradius;
538  maxs[i] = origin[i] + boxradius;
539  }
540 
541  numListedEntities = trap_EntitiesInBox(mins, maxs, entityList, MAX_GENTITIES);
542 
543  for (e = 0 ; e < numListedEntities ; e++)
544  {
545  ent = &g_entities[entityList[e]];
546 
547  if (!ent->r.bmodel)
548  {
549  VectorSubtract(ent->r.currentOrigin, origin, v);
550  }
551  else
552  {
553  for (i = 0 ; i < 3 ; i++)
554  {
555  if (origin[i] < ent->r.absmin[i])
556  {
557  v[i] = ent->r.absmin[i] - origin[i];
558  }
559  else if (origin[i] > ent->r.absmax[i])
560  {
561  v[i] = origin[i] - ent->r.absmax[i];
562  }
563  else
564  {
565  v[i] = 0;
566  }
567  }
568  }
569 
570  dist = VectorLength(v);
571  if (dist >= radius)
572  {
573  continue;
574  }
575 
576  if (CanDamage(ent, origin))
577  {
578  damagedList[numDamaged++] = entityList[e];
579  }
580  else
581  {
582  VectorAdd(ent->r.absmin, ent->r.absmax, midpoint);
583  VectorScale(midpoint, 0.5f, midpoint);
584  VectorCopy(midpoint, dest);
585 
586  trap_Trace(&tr, origin, vec3_origin, vec3_origin, dest, ENTITYNUM_NONE, MASK_SOLID);
587  if (tr.fraction < 1.0f)
588  {
589  VectorSubtract(dest, origin, dest);
590  dist = VectorLength(dest);
591  if (dist < radius * 0.2f) // closer than 1/4 dist
592  {
593  damagedList[numDamaged++] = entityList[e];
594  }
595  }
596  }
597  }
598 
599  return numDamaged;
600 }

657 static void HandleEntsThatBlockConstructible(gentity_t *constructor, gentity_t *constructible, qboolean handleBlockingEnts, qboolean warnBlockingPlayers)
658 {
659  // check if something blocks us
660  int constructibleList[MAX_GENTITIES];
661  int entityList[MAX_GENTITIES];
662  int blockingList[MAX_GENTITIES];
663  int constructibleEntities = 0;
664  int listedEntities, e;
665  int blockingEntities = 0;
666  gentity_t *check, *block;
667  // backup...
668  int constructibleModelindex = constructible->s.modelindex;
669  int constructibleClipmask = constructible->clipmask;
670  int constructibleContents = constructible->r.contents;
671  int constructibleNonSolidBModel = (constructible->s.eFlags & EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL);
672 
673  trap_SetBrushModel(constructible, va("*%i", constructible->s.modelindex2));
674 
675  // ...and restore
676  constructible->clipmask = constructibleClipmask;
677  constructible->r.contents = constructibleContents;
678  if (!constructibleNonSolidBModel)
679  {
680  constructible->s.eFlags &= ~EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
681  }
682  trap_LinkEntity(constructible);
683 
684  // store our origin
685  VectorCopy(constructible->r.absmin, constructible->s.origin2);
686  VectorAdd(constructible->r.absmax, constructible->s.origin2, constructible->s.origin2);
687  VectorScale(constructible->s.origin2, 0.5f, constructible->s.origin2);
688 
689  // get all the entities that make up the constructible
690  if (constructible->track && constructible->track[0])
691  {
692  vec3_t mins, maxs;
693 
694  VectorCopy(constructible->r.absmin, mins);
695  VectorCopy(constructible->r.absmax, maxs);
696 
697  check = NULL;
698 
699  while (1)
700  {
701  check = G_Find(check, FOFS(track), constructible->track);
702 
703  if (check == constructible)
704  {
705  continue;
706  }
707 
708  if (!check)
709  {
710  break;
711  }
712 
713  if (constructible->count2)
714  {
715  if (check->partofstage != constructible->grenadeFired)
716  {
717  continue;
718  }
719  }
720 
721  // get the bounding box of all entities in the constructible together
722  AddPointToBounds(check->r.absmin, mins, maxs);
723  AddPointToBounds(check->r.absmax, mins, maxs);
724 
725  constructibleList[constructibleEntities++] = check->s.number;
726  }
727 
728  listedEntities = trap_EntitiesInBox(mins, maxs, entityList, MAX_GENTITIES);
729 
730  // make our constructible entities solid so we can check against them
731  //trap_LinkEntity( constructible );
732  MakeTemporarySolid(constructible);
733  for (e = 0; e < constructibleEntities; e++)
734  {
735  check = &g_entities[constructibleList[e]];
736 
737  //trap_LinkEntity( check );
738  MakeTemporarySolid(check);
739  }
740  }
741  else
742  {
743  // changed * to abs*
744  listedEntities = trap_EntitiesInBox(constructible->r.absmin, constructible->r.absmax, entityList, MAX_GENTITIES);
745 
746  // make our constructible solid so we can check against it
747  //trap_LinkEntity( constructible );
748  MakeTemporarySolid(constructible);
749  }
750 
751  for (e = 0; e < listedEntities; e++)
752  {
753  check = &g_entities[entityList[e]];
754 
755  // ignore everything but items, players and missiles (grenades too)
756  if (check->s.eType != ET_MISSILE && check->s.eType != ET_ITEM && check->s.eType != ET_PLAYER && !check->physicsObject)
757  {
758  continue;
759  }
760 
761  // remove any corpses, this includes dynamite
762  if (check->r.contents == CONTENTS_CORPSE)
763  {
764  blockingList[blockingEntities++] = entityList[e];
765  continue;
766  }
767 
768  // FIXME: dynamite seems to test out of position?
769  // see if the entity is in a solid now
770  if ((block = G_TestEntityPosition(check)) == NULL)
771  {
772  continue;
773  }
774 
775  // the entity is blocked and it is a player, then warn the player
776  if (warnBlockingPlayers && check->s.eType == ET_PLAYER)
777  {
778  if ((level.time - check->client->lastConstructibleBlockingWarnTime) >= MIN_BLOCKINGWARNING_INTERVAL)
779  {
780  trap_SendServerCommand(check->s.number, "cp \"Warning, leave the construction area...\" 1");
781  check->client->lastConstructibleBlockingWarnTime = level.time;
782  }
783  }
784 
785  blockingList[blockingEntities++] = entityList[e];
786  }
787 
788  // undo the temporary solid for our entities
789  UndoTemporarySolid(constructible);
790  if (constructible->track && constructible->track[0])
791  {
792  for (e = 0; e < constructibleEntities; e++)
793  {
794  check = &g_entities[constructibleList[e]];
795 
796  //trap_UnlinkEntity( check );
797  UndoTemporarySolid(check);
798  }
799  }
800 
801  if (handleBlockingEnts)
802  {
803  for (e = 0; e < blockingEntities; e++)
804  {
805  block = &g_entities[blockingList[e]];
806 
807  if (block->client || block->s.eType == ET_CORPSE)
808  {
809  G_Damage(block, constructible, constructor, NULL, NULL, GIB_DAMAGE(block->health), DAMAGE_NO_PROTECTION, MOD_CRUSH_CONSTRUCTION);
810  }
811  else if (block->s.eType == ET_ITEM && block->item->giType == IT_TEAM)
812  {
813  // see if it's a critical entity, one that we can't just simply kill (basically flags)
814  Team_DroppedFlagThink(block);
815  }
816  else
817  {
818  // remove the landmine from both teamlists
819  if (block->s.eType == ET_MISSILE && block->methodOfDeath == MOD_LANDMINE)
820  {
821  mapEntityData_t *mEnt;
822 
823  if ((mEnt = G_FindMapEntityData(&mapEntityData[0], block - g_entities)) != NULL)
824  {
825  G_FreeMapEntityData(&mapEntityData[0], mEnt);
826  }
827 
828  if ((mEnt = G_FindMapEntityData(&mapEntityData[1], block - g_entities)) != NULL)
829  {
830  G_FreeMapEntityData(&mapEntityData[1], mEnt);
831  }
832  }
833 
834  // just get rid of it
835  G_FreeEntity(block);
836  }
837  }
838  }
839 
840  if (constructibleModelindex)
841  {
842  trap_SetBrushModel(constructible, va("*%i", constructibleModelindex));
843  // ...and restore
844  constructible->clipmask = constructibleClipmask;
845  constructible->r.contents = constructibleContents;
846  if (!constructibleNonSolidBModel)
847  {
848  constructible->s.eFlags &= ~EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
849  }
850  trap_LinkEntity(constructible);
851  }
852  else
853  {
854  constructible->s.modelindex = 0;
855  //constructible->clipmask = constructibleClipmask;
856  //constructible->r.contents = constructibleContents;
857  //if( !constructibleNonSolidBModel )
858  // constructible->s.eFlags &= ~EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
859  trap_LinkEntity(constructible);
860  }
861 }

874 static qboolean TryConstructing(gentity_t *ent)
875 {
876  gentity_t *constructible = ent->client->touchingTOI->target_ent;
877 
878  // no construction during prematch
879  if (level.warmupTime)
880  {
881  return qfalse;
882  }
883 
884  // see if we are in a trigger_objective_info targetting multiple func_constructibles
885  if (constructible->s.eType == ET_CONSTRUCTIBLE && ent->client->touchingTOI->chain)
886  {
887  gentity_t *otherconstructible = NULL;
888 
889  // use the target that has the same team as the player
890  if (constructible->s.teamNum != ent->client->sess.sessionTeam)
891  {
892  constructible = ent->client->touchingTOI->chain;
893  }
894 
895  otherconstructible = constructible->chain;
896 
897  // make sure the other constructible isn't built/underconstruction/something
898  if (otherconstructible->s.angles2[0] != 0.f ||
899  otherconstructible->s.angles2[1] != 0.f ||
900  (otherconstructible->count2 && otherconstructible->grenadeFired))
901  {
902  return qfalse;
903  }
904  }
905 
906  // see if we are in a trigger_objective_info targetting a func_constructible
907  if (constructible->s.eType == ET_CONSTRUCTIBLE &&
908  constructible->s.teamNum == ent->client->sess.sessionTeam)
909  {
910  // constructible xp sharing
911  float addhealth;
912  float xpperround;
913 
914  if (constructible->s.angles2[0] >= 250) // have to do this so we don't score multiple times
915  {
916  return qfalse;
917  }
918 
919  if (constructible->s.angles2[1] != 0.f)
920  {
921  return qfalse;
922  }
923 
924  // Check if we can construct - updates the classWeaponTime as well
925  if (!ReadyToConstruct(ent, constructible, qtrue))
926  {
927  return qtrue;
928  }
929 
930  // try to start building
931  if (constructible->s.angles2[0] <= 0)
932  {
933  // wait a bit, this prevents network spam
934  if (level.time - constructible->lastHintCheckTime < CONSTRUCT_POSTDECAY_TIME)
935  {
936  return qtrue; // likely will come back soon - so override other plier bits anyway
937  }
938 
939  // swap brushmodels if staged
940  if (constructible->count2)
941  {
942  constructible->grenadeFired++;
943  constructible->s.modelindex2 = constructible->conbmodels[constructible->grenadeFired - 1];
944  //trap_SetBrushModel( constructible, va( "*%i", constructible->conbmodels[constructible->grenadeFired-1] ) );
945  }
946 
947  G_SetEntState(constructible, STATE_UNDERCONSTRUCTION);
948 
949  if (!constructible->count2)
950  {
951  // call script
952  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "buildstart", "final");
953  constructible->s.frame = 1;
954  }
955  else
956  {
957  if (constructible->grenadeFired == constructible->count2)
958  {
959  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "buildstart", "final");
960  constructible->s.frame = constructible->grenadeFired;
961  }
962  else
963  {
964  switch (constructible->grenadeFired)
965  {
966  case 1:
967  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "buildstart", "stage1");
968  constructible->s.frame = 1;
969  break;
970  case 2:
971  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "buildstart", "stage2");
972  constructible->s.frame = 2;
973  break;
974  case 3:
975  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "buildstart", "stage3");
976  constructible->s.frame = 3;
977  break;
978  default:
979  break;
980  }
981  }
982  }
983 
984  if (ent->client->touchingTOI->chain && ent->client->touchingTOI->count2)
985  {
986  // find the constructible indicator and change team
987  mapEntityData_t *mEnt;
988  mapEntityData_Team_t *teamList;
989  gentity_t *indicator = &g_entities[ent->client->touchingTOI->count2];
990 
991  indicator->s.teamNum = constructible->s.teamNum;
992 
993  // update the map for the other team
994  teamList = indicator->s.teamNum == TEAM_AXIS ? &mapEntityData[1] : &mapEntityData[0]; // inversed
995  if ((mEnt = G_FindMapEntityData(teamList, indicator - g_entities)) != NULL)
996  {
997  G_FreeMapEntityData(teamList, mEnt);
998  }
999  }
1000 
1001  if (!constructible->count2 || constructible->grenadeFired == 1)
1002  {
1003  // link in if we just started building
1004  G_UseEntity(constructible, ent->client->touchingTOI, ent);
1005  }
1006 
1007  // setup our think function for decaying
1008  constructible->think = func_constructible_underconstructionthink;
1009  constructible->nextthink = level.time + FRAMETIME;
1010 
1011  G_PrintClientSpammyCenterPrint(ent - g_entities, "Constructing...");
1012  }
1013 
1014  if (!ent->client->constructSoundTime || level.time > ent->client->constructSoundTime)
1015  {
1016  // construction sound sent as event (was temp entity)
1017  G_AddEvent(ent, EV_GENERAL_SOUND, GAMESOUND_WORLD_BUILD);
1018  ent->client->constructSoundTime = level.time + 4000; // duration of sound
1019  }
1020 
1021  // constructible xp sharing
1022  addhealth = (255.f / (constructible->constructibleStats.duration / (float)FRAMETIME));
1023  xpperround = constructible->constructibleStats.constructxpbonus / (255.f / addhealth) + 0.01f;
1024  G_AddSkillPoints(ent, SK_EXPLOSIVES_AND_CONSTRUCTION, xpperround);
1025  G_DebugAddSkillPoints(ent, SK_EXPLOSIVES_AND_CONSTRUCTION, xpperround, "construction sharing.");
1026 
1027  // Give health until it is full, don't continue
1028  constructible->s.angles2[0] += addhealth;
1029 
1030  if (constructible->s.angles2[0] >= 250)
1031  {
1032  constructible->s.angles2[0] = 0;
1033  HandleEntsThatBlockConstructible(ent, constructible, qtrue, qfalse);
1034  }
1035  else
1036  {
1037  constructible->lastHintCheckTime = level.time;
1038  HandleEntsThatBlockConstructible(ent, constructible, qfalse, qtrue);
1039  return qtrue; // properly constructed
1040  }
1041 
1042  if (constructible->count2)
1043  {
1044  // backup...
1045  int constructibleClipmask = constructible->clipmask;
1046  int constructibleContents = constructible->r.contents;
1047  int constructibleNonSolidBModel = (constructible->s.eFlags & EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL);
1048 
1049  constructible->s.modelindex2 = 0;
1050  trap_SetBrushModel(constructible, va("*%i", constructible->conbmodels[constructible->grenadeFired - 1]));
1051 
1052  // ...and restore
1053  constructible->clipmask = constructibleClipmask;
1054  constructible->r.contents = constructibleContents;
1055  if (!constructibleNonSolidBModel)
1056  {
1057  constructible->s.eFlags &= ~EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
1058  }
1059 
1060  if (constructible->grenadeFired == constructible->count2)
1061  {
1062  constructible->s.angles2[1] = 1;
1063  }
1064  }
1065  else
1066  {
1067  // backup...
1068  int constructibleClipmask = constructible->clipmask;
1069  int constructibleContents = constructible->r.contents;
1070  int constructibleNonSolidBModel = (constructible->s.eFlags & EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL);
1071 
1072  constructible->s.modelindex2 = 0;
1073  trap_SetBrushModel(constructible, constructible->model);
1074 
1075  // ...and restore
1076  constructible->clipmask = constructibleClipmask;
1077  constructible->r.contents = constructibleContents;
1078  if (!constructibleNonSolidBModel)
1079  {
1080  constructible->s.eFlags &= ~EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
1081  }
1082 
1083  constructible->s.angles2[1] = 1;
1084  }
1085 
1086  // unlink the objective info to get rid of the indicator for now
1087  // don't unlink, we still want the location popup. Instead, constructible_indicator_think got changed to free
1088  // the indicator when the constructible is constructed
1089  //if( constructible->parent )
1090  // trap_UnlinkEntity( constructible->parent );
1091 
1092  G_SetEntState(constructible, STATE_DEFAULT);
1093 
1094  // make destructable
1095  if (!(constructible->spawnflags & 2))
1096  {
1097  constructible->takedamage = qtrue;
1098  constructible->health = constructible->sound1to2;
1099  }
1100 
1101  // Stop thinking
1102  constructible->think = NULL;
1103  constructible->nextthink = 0;
1104 
1105  if (!constructible->count2)
1106  {
1107  // call script
1108  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "built", "final");
1109  }
1110  else
1111  {
1112  if (constructible->grenadeFired == constructible->count2)
1113  {
1114  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "built", "final");
1115  }
1116  else
1117  {
1118  switch (constructible->grenadeFired)
1119  {
1120  case 1:
1121  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "built", "stage1");
1122  break;
1123  case 2:
1124  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "built", "stage2");
1125  break;
1126  case 3:
1127  G_Script_ScriptEvent(constructible, "built", "stage3");
1128  break;
1129  default:
1130  break;
1131  }
1132  }
1133  }
1134 
1135  // Stop sound
1136  if (constructible->parent->spawnflags & 8)
1137  {
1138  constructible->parent->s.loopSound = 0;
1139  }
1140  else
1141  {
1142  constructible->s.loopSound = 0;
1143  }
1144 
1145  //ent->client->ps.classWeaponTime = level.time; // Out of "ammo"
1146 
1147  // if not invulnerable and dynamite-able, create a 'destructable' marker for the other team
1148  if (!(constructible->spawnflags & CONSTRUCTIBLE_INVULNERABLE) && (constructible->constructibleStats.weaponclass >= 1))
1149  {
1150  if (!constructible->count2 || constructible->grenadeFired == 1)
1151  {
1152  gentity_t *tent = NULL;
1153  gentity_t *e;
1154 
1155  e = G_Spawn();
1156  e->r.svFlags = SVF_BROADCAST;
1157  e->classname = "explosive_indicator";
1158  e->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
1159  e->s.eType = ET_EXPLOSIVE_INDICATOR;
1160 
1161  // Find the trigger_objective_info that targets us (if not set before)
1162  while ((tent = G_Find(tent, FOFS(target), constructible->targetname)) != NULL)
1163  {
1164  if (tent->s.eType == ET_OID_TRIGGER)
1165  {
1166  if (tent->spawnflags & 8)
1167  {
1168  e->s.eType = ET_TANK_INDICATOR;
1169  }
1170  e->parent = tent;
1171  }
1172  }
1173 
1174  if (constructible->spawnflags & AXIS_CONSTRUCTIBLE)
1175  {
1176  e->s.teamNum = TEAM_AXIS;
1177  }
1178  else if (constructible->spawnflags & ALLIED_CONSTRUCTIBLE)
1179  {
1180  e->s.teamNum = TEAM_ALLIES;
1181  }
1182 
1183  e->s.modelindex2 = ent->client->touchingTOI->s.teamNum;
1184  e->r.ownerNum = constructible->s.number;
1185  e->think = explosive_indicator_think;
1186  e->nextthink = level.time + FRAMETIME;
1187 
1188  e->s.effect1Time = constructible->constructibleStats.weaponclass;
1189 
1190  if (constructible->parent->tagParent)
1191  {
1192  e->tagParent = constructible->parent->tagParent;
1193  Q_strncpyz(e->tagName, constructible->parent->tagName, MAX_QPATH);
1194  }
1195  else
1196  {
1197  VectorCopy(constructible->r.absmin, e->s.pos.trBase);
1198  VectorAdd(constructible->r.absmax, e->s.pos.trBase, e->s.pos.trBase);
1199  VectorScale(e->s.pos.trBase, 0.5f, e->s.pos.trBase);
1200  }
1201 
1202  SnapVector(e->s.pos.trBase);
1203 
1204  trap_LinkEntity(e);
1205  }
1206  else
1207  {
1208  gentity_t *check;
1209  int i;
1210 
1211  // find our marker and update it's coordinates
1212  for (i = 0, check = g_entities; i < level.num_entities; i++, check++)
1213  {
1214  if (check->s.eType != ET_EXPLOSIVE_INDICATOR && check->s.eType != ET_TANK_INDICATOR && check->s.eType != ET_TANK_INDICATOR_DEAD)
1215  {
1216  continue;
1217  }
1218 
1219  if (check->r.ownerNum == constructible->s.number)
1220  {
1221  // found it!
1222  if (constructible->parent->tagParent)
1223  {
1224  check->tagParent = constructible->parent->tagParent;
1225  Q_strncpyz(check->tagName, constructible->parent->tagName, MAX_QPATH);
1226  }
1227  else
1228  {
1229  VectorCopy(constructible->r.absmin, check->s.pos.trBase);
1230  VectorAdd(constructible->r.absmax, check->s.pos.trBase, check->s.pos.trBase);
1231  VectorScale(check->s.pos.trBase, 0.5f, check->s.pos.trBase);
1232 
1233  SnapVector(check->s.pos.trBase);
1234  }
1235 
1236  trap_LinkEntity(check);
1237  break;
1238  }
1239  }
1240  }
1241  }
1242 
1243  return qtrue; // building
1244  }
1245 
1246  return qfalse;
1247 }

2739

2762

3600  upangle += 0.5f; // 0.0 / 1.0

3602  if (upangle < .1f)

3936 void CalcMuzzlePoints(gentity_t *ent, int weapon)
3937 {
3938  vec3_t viewang;
3939 
3940  VectorCopy(ent->client->ps.viewangles, viewang);
3941 
3942  // non ai's take into account scoped weapon 'sway' (just another way aimspread is visualized/utilized)
3943 
3944  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_SCOPED)
3945  {
3946  float pitchMinAmp, yawMinAmp, phase;
3947 
3948  if (weapon == WP_FG42SCOPE)
3949  {
3950  pitchMinAmp = 4 * ZOOM_PITCH_MIN_AMPLITUDE;
3951  yawMinAmp = 4 * ZOOM_YAW_MIN_AMPLITUDE;
3952  }
3953  else
3954  {
3955  pitchMinAmp = ZOOM_PITCH_MIN_AMPLITUDE;
3956  yawMinAmp = ZOOM_YAW_MIN_AMPLITUDE;
3957  }
3958 
3959  // rotate 'forward' vector by the sway
3960  phase = level.time / 1000.0f * ZOOM_PITCH_FREQUENCY * M_TAU_F;
3961  viewang[PITCH] += ZOOM_PITCH_AMPLITUDE * (float)sin((double)phase) * (ent->client->currentAimSpreadScale + pitchMinAmp);
3962 
3963  phase = level.time / 1000.0f * ZOOM_YAW_FREQUENCY * M_TAU_F;
3964  viewang[YAW] += ZOOM_YAW_AMPLITUDE * (float)sin((double)phase) * (ent->client->currentAimSpreadScale + yawMinAmp);
3965  }
3966 
3967  // set aiming directions
3968  AngleVectors(viewang, forward, right, up);
3969 
3970  // modified the muzzle stuff so that weapons that need to fire down a perfect trace
3971  // straight out of the camera (SP5, Mauser right now) can have that accuracy, but
3972  // weapons that need an offset effect (bazooka/grenade/etc.) can still look like
3973  // they came out of the weap.
3974  CalcMuzzlePointForActivate(ent, forward, right, up, muzzleTrace);
3975  CalcMuzzlePoint(ent, weapon, forward, right, up, muzzleEffect);
3976 }

4102 void FireWeapon(gentity_t *ent)
4103 {
4104  // dead guys don't fire guns
4105  if (ent->client->ps.pm_type == PM_DEAD)
4106  {
4107  return;
4108  }
4109 
4110  // mg42
4111  if (ent->client->ps.persistant[PERS_HWEAPON_USE] && ent->active)
4112  {
4113  return;
4114  }
4115 
4116  // need to call this for AI prediction also
4117  CalcMuzzlePoints(ent, ent->s.weapon);
4118 
4119  // specific firing handle for artillery using binocular
4120  if ((ent->client->ps.eFlags & EF_ZOOMING) && (ent->client->ps.stats[STAT_KEYS] & (1 << INV_BINOCS)))
4121  {
4122  if (ent->client->sess.playerType == PC_FIELDOPS)
4123  {
4124  if (ent->client->ps.leanf == 0.f)
4125  {
4126  Weapon_Artillery(ent);
4127  }
4128  return;
4129  }
4130  }
4131 
4132  // covert ops disguise handling
4133  if (ent->client->ps.powerups[PW_OPS_DISGUISED])
4134  {
4135  if (!(GetWeaponTableData(ent->s.weapon)->attributes & WEAPON_ATTRIBUT_NEVER_LOST_DESGUISE))
4136  {
4137  if (!(GetWeaponTableData(ent->s.weapon)->attributes & WEAPON_ATTRIBUT_KEEP_DESGUISE) || G_PlayerCanBeSeenByOthers(ent))
4138  {
4139  ent->client->ps.powerups[PW_OPS_DISGUISED] = 0;
4140  ent->client->disguiseClientNum = -1;
4141  }
4142  }
4143  }
4144 
4145  // fire the specific weapon
4146  if (weapFireTable[ent->s.weapon].fire)
4147  {
4148  gentity_t *pFiredShot = NULL; // Omni-bot To tell bots about projectiles
4149 #ifdef FEATURE_LUA
4150  if (!G_LuaHook_WeaponFire(ent->s.number, ent->s.weapon, &pFiredShot))
4151 #endif
4152  {
4153  pFiredShot = weapFireTable[ent->s.weapon].fire(ent);
4154  }
4155 
4156 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
4157  // Omni-bot - Send a fire event.
4158  if (pFiredShot)
4159  {
4160  Bot_Event_FireWeapon(ent - g_entities, Bot_WeaponGameToBot(ent->s.weapon), pFiredShot);
4161  }
4162 #endif
4163  }
4164 
4165 #ifndef DEBUG_STATS
4166  if (g_gamestate.integer == GS_PLAYING)
4167 #endif
4168 
4169  ent->client->sess.aWeaponStats[GetWeaponTableData(ent->s.weapon)->indexWeaponStat].atts++;
4170 }
